My husband and I used to dine here when we lived within walking distant and we were never disappointed. Now, we order delivery and it’s rare for a place to “pull it off” the same way it does through delivery versus dining in. It is just unreal how good and fresh this food is. Personally, I can’t get over the falafel sandwich. I have branched out in the past with the kale salad and that was amazing too. We have ordered almost every hummus and my husband ends up eating any leftover with a damn spoon. I can’t even begin to explain the hot sauce...the red is an addictive drug(I promise I’m not being dramatic) and the green is just as good. I just smother them both on every piece of my food and over indulge happily every time. Just needed to take the time to let everyone here know, it’s worth every penny and this business deserves to stay around and receive every accolade imaginable. Thank you!

Food here is too expensive, plates too small & meh. Not worth coming back.  For 2 people we shared a Main and picked 3 different Meze items, but only the Morocan Eggplant was good. At $19 for 3 sides- each of them were small, 2 of them were not very good, and none of it came with any pita. We had to order bread for more money, so we wouldn't have to eat straight dips and spreads off of forks. Our Rice Majadra main also did not come with pita, and was good-not-great. Overall a disappointing trip.  2 other tables around us ordered lunch specials while we were there, and we heard them both complain/laugh to the waitress about the small size of the included side. They came in on tiny plate the size of a soy sauce dish, about one bites worth.

Exceptional Mediterranean food in a quaint, low key setting. Dishes were well presented; if ordering hummus falafel plate (which I recommend), homemade hummus, drizzled with flavorful olive oil, topped with crispy, herbaceous falafel with a choice of regular or whole wheat pita comes to your table hot out of the oven. Also chose 3 Meze Market dishes: roasted cauliflower, roasted red peppers with garlic and a roasted sweet potato dish. I can’t recommend this spot enough. You will not leave disappointed or hungry! Looking forward to eating here in the spring to enjoy their back patio dining.

This place is a five stars. I am currently at Hummus Market, for probably the 10th time in the past 8 weeks ;)! After 6 years in NY, I only find Hummus Market now. Finally a place where I can enjoy the delights of Mediterranean Foods. They use very fresh ingredients, everything is made fresh to order. Each day I am looking forward to the next time I’ll have lunch there. I’ll be very sad to go back to work after my maternity leave for that reason!! (And to leave my baby of course! Don’t get me wrong;)) I really can’t stand to go to fancy and overrated  places anymore where the food is so average!! Hummus Market is now in my top 3 restaurants in NYC/Brooklyn. Simple, delicious, fair prices, refined, perfectly cooked. The roasted eggplant are so soft/melting in your mouth. Rice Majadra is to die for. And so is the lentil soup!! So mouthwatering just by writing my review !! Nice backyard in the shade. If you are a foodie, go there and be adventurous! Don’t go for typical things, try what you don’t find in other Mediterranean restaurant. That’s my opinion of course, you do whatever you want;) Just enjoy

Really delicious & simple homey food made with love and care. Kale salad, sweet potato latkes, all of the hummus, Israeli cous cous, falafel, and mushroom special (meorav) are my favorites. Lats week my friend and me had lunch there. With a 20% tip, our bill came down to $18.79 per person, so we split the bill. A couple of days later I discovered that the restaurant charged my credit card twice. I called them and spoke to the same waiter, she promised they would call me back. They did not. The next day I called again, another water told me they'd call me back. They did not. I skipped the third day. On the fourth day I called again, politely asking where is my money. Another waiter did not have patience to listen to my story and she passed the phone to a guy who introduced himself as an owner. He told me he called the bank and would get back to me when he had an answer from the bank. Just like that, no apologies, no "we would like you to keep coming here, here is a $20 gift card for your next dinner" - nothing. Great jobs, guys! If I get my money back, I will add the note here.

I love Hummus Market and I would have given them another star but I'm deducting it for the following conversation.  My friend and I were having lunch. Friend to Waiter: Can I get a diet coke please? Waiter: We don't have diet coke or any fizzy drinks. (Me --- thinking there better be an amazing reason why they don't serve diet coke --- I turn to the waiter: Why don't you serve diet coke?) Waiter: We want people to understand we're not a cheap take out spot. We're a high end restaurant so no diet coke. Me to waiter: You do realize there are Michelin Star restaurants who serve diet coke. Case closed.  Ok back to how great the food is. Yes, they have a kickass shakshuka. Yes they have amazing small plate dishes. The watermelon salad, tomato salad both heavenly dishes. Their pita is fresh out of this world especially with their made in house hummus. I am a huge fan of their foods. I doubt there's anything on the menu that's not top notch perfection.  I've definitely been here more than once and every time the food is consistent and delicious.  The decor is lovely and rustic, they do have an amazing backyard in the summer time. Waitstaff is mostly on point, friendly and helpful and prices are quite reasonable.  I will keep coming back for more, although I'm hoping they'll put the no diet coke policy aside and start serving it.  They can even put a lemon on the edge for a posh effect (like every damn hotel and restaurant in the city) :)
